HEADWORD: Cœlospermous
<hw>C⟦oe⟧l`o*sper"mous</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ <?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>koi^los</grk> hollow + <?/ seed.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Hollow-seeded; having the ventral face of the seedlike carpels
incurved at the ends, as in coriander seed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

